Implement a full veterinary clinic management Blazor Web App. The project is already scaffolded at /tmp/sv-4aa1e00ddbaf47cda5f52d602a39ec14/VetClinic with Interactive Server global mode and Individual authentication.

## Current state
- .NET 11 preview, Blazor Web App with `-int Server -ai -au Individual`
- SQLite database with Identity already configured
- Template pages (Counter.razor, Weather.razor, Auth.razor) need to be removed
- App.razor uses `PageRenderMode` pattern for global interactivity

## What to implement

### 1. Domain Models (create /Data/Models/ directory)

Create these entity classes:

**Owner.cs**
```csharp
namespace VetClinic.Data.Models;

public class Owner
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string FirstName { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string LastName { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Phone { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Email { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Address { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public DateTime CreatedAt { get; set; } = DateTime.UtcNow;
    public List<Pet> Pets { get; set; } = new();
}
```

**Pet.cs**
```csharp
namespace VetClinic.Data.Models;

public class Pet
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string Name { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Species { get; set; } = string.Empty; // Dog, Cat, Bird, etc.
    public string Breed { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public DateTime DateOfBirth { get; set; }
    public decimal Weight { get; set; }
    public string Microchip { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public int OwnerId { get; set; }
    public Owner Owner { get; set; } = null!;
    public List<Treatment> Treatments { get; set; } = new();
    public List<Appointment> Appointments { get; set; } = new();
}
```

**Treatment.cs**
```csharp
namespace VetClinic.Data.Models;

public class Treatment
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
